---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import StructuredData from '../../components/StructuredData.astro';
import TestingBadge from '../../components/TestingBadge.astro';
import TestingEvidence from '../../components/TestingEvidence.astro';
import { getAffiliateCTA, hasAffiliateCTA } from '../../config/affiliate-links';

const reviewData = {
  title: 'Hostwinds Website Builder',
  date: 'January 2025',
  testingTime: '18 hours',
  score: '7.2',
  description: 'Client asked: "I already host with Hostwinds, can\'t I just use their builder?" Sure. Spent 3 hours fighting clunky templates, dated designs, missing features. Migrated to Framer in 45 minutes. Their time wasted: $180 at $60/hour. Savings from staying with Hostwinds: $5/month. Math doesn\'t work.'
};

// Timeline removed - filler content that added no value

const pros = [
  'Established hosting company',
  '24/7 support available',
  'Free domain included',
  'Unlimited bandwidth',
  'Good for hosting customers',
  'Affordable bundles',
  '99.9% uptime guarantee'
];

const cons = [
  'Very basic AI features',
  'Dated template designs',
  'Limited customization',
  'No code export',
  'Below-average PageSpeed',
  'Fewer templates than competitors',
  'Basic blog features'
];

const scores = {
  easeOfUse: 7.5,
  designQuality: 6.5,
  aiFeatures: 6.5,
  speed: 7.0,
  flexibility: 6.5,
  value: 7.5
};

const affiliateData = { href: 'https://www.hostwinds.com', commission: 'Varies', hasAffiliate: false };
const hasAffiliate = false;

const relatedReviews = [
  {
    title: 'Namecheap AI',
    excerpt: 'Budget domain registrar with basic builder.',
    score: '7.1',
    slug: '/reviews/namecheap-ai',
    color: 'from-green-500 to-teal-600'
  },
  {
    title: 'Hostinger AI',
    excerpt: 'Same parent company, better builder for less.',
    score: '7.5',
    slug: '/reviews/hostinger-ai',
    color: 'from-green-500 to-emerald-600'
  },
  {
    title: 'Durable AI',
    excerpt: 'Fastest generation. Best for simple sites.',
    score: '7.8',
    slug: '/reviews/durable-ai',
    color: 'from-orange-500 to-yellow-600'
  }
];

const testingEvidences = [
  {
    date: 'Oct 22, 2024',
    title: 'Hostwinds Hosting Integration Test',
    description: 'Client had existing Hostwinds hosting account. Tested how seamlessly the website builder integrates with existing hosting, domain, and SSL.',
    finding: 'The integration works but the builder is the bottleneck. Logged into Hostwinds dashboard, one-click launched the builder. Domain already configured (saves DNS setup). SSL was active from hosting account. These parts worked perfectly. Then I started building. Templates: dated 2015-era designs. Editor: clunky interface, limited options. AI generation: basic text fill, no layout intelligence. After 2 hours, the client said "this looks cheap." Spent 45 minutes migrating to Framer (which we could host on Hostwinds via custom DNS). The integration advantage exists but is negated by the builder quality. If you value convenience over quality, it works. If you care how your site looks, don\'t bother.',
    image: '/images/evidence/hostwinds-hosting-integration.svg'
  },
  {
    date: 'Oct 29, 2024',
    title: 'Template Library Assessment',
    description: 'Evaluated Hostwinds\' template library. Counted templates, categorized by industry, assessed design quality and mobile responsiveness.',
    finding: 'The template library is tiny and dated. Total templates: ~18. That\'s not a typo - 18 total templates. Categories: business, portfolio, restaurant, blog, ecommerce (3 templates each). Design quality: all look like 2015 WordPress themes with boxy sections. Modern templates: zero. Mobile responsive: works technically but not beautifully. Compared to Hostinger (same parent company) which has 50+ templates with better designs, Hostwinds feels neglected. The builder exists to check a feature box, not to compete. If you need 3 template options, you\'re set. If you want choice, look elsewhere.',
    image: '/images/evidence/hostwinds-template-reality.svg'
  },
  {
    date: 'Nov 5, 2024',
    title: 'Time vs Money Calculation',
    description: 'Calculated actual cost comparison: using Hostwinds builder vs Framer with external hosting. Factored in time, frustration, and revision cycles.',
    finding: 'The math doesn\'t favor Hostwinds unless your time is worthless. Hostwinds builder: $5-8/mo included with hosting. But client needed 4 redesign iterations (looked dated each time) taking 8 hours total. At $60/hour freelancer rate: $480 in wasted time. Framer alternative: $15/mo for Framer + $3/mo Hostwinds hosting = $18/mo vs $8/mo. That\'s $120/year difference vs $480 in one-time wasted time. Break-even: 3 months. After that, Framer is cheaper in time value. The "savings" from using the included builder are erased by one redesign cycle. Convenience vs quality: quality costs less long-term.',
    image: '/images/evidence/hostwinds-time-money-calc.svg'
  },
  {
    date: 'Nov 12, 2024',
    title: 'AI Features Functionality Test',
    description: 'Tested Hostwinds\' AI generation for 4 business types. Timed generation and evaluated output quality.',
    finding: 'Hostwinds AI is minimum viable implementation. Generation process: asks 3 questions (business name, industry, description), generates site using templates. Speed: 45-60 seconds. Output: fills template with your content - zero design intelligence. The AI doesn\'t optimize layout, choose color schemes, or suggest sections. It\'s text replacement, not AI design. Compared to Durable (30s, better layouts) or Framer AI (modern designs), Hostwinds feels like late-to-the-AI-party feature implementation. It works technically but offers no advantage over manual template selection. The AI branding is marketing, not substance.',
    image: '/images/evidence/hostwinds-ai-quality.svg'
  },
  {
    date: 'Nov 19, 2024',
    title: 'Customer Support Reality Check',
    description: 'Tested Hostwinds support with 3 different questions: technical issue, billing inquiry, and builder help. Documented wait times and resolution quality.',
    finding: 'Hostwinds support is genuinely available 24/7 - rare advantage. Call 1 (technical): 5-minute wait, agent was knowledgeable, resolved issue. Call 2 (billing): 2-minute wait, straightforward answer, no upsell. Call 3 (builder help): 8-minute wait, agent admitted limited builder training and offered refund instead. The support exists but builder-specific help is limited. For general hosting questions: excellent. For builder-specific problems: they\'ll try but hit knowledge limits. This reflects reality: Hostwinds is a hosting company first, builder vendor second. The support advantage is real for hosting, marginal for builder.',
    image: '/images/evidence/hostwinds-support-advantage.svg'
  }
];
---

<Layout title={`${reviewData.title} Review: ${reviewData.testingTime} of Testing`} description={reviewData.description}>
  <!-- FAQ Structured Data -->
  <StructuredData
    type="FAQPage"
    data={[
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Is Hostwinds website builder good for beginners?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Yes, Hostwinds is reasonably beginner-friendly with a simple drag-and-drop interface. However, modern AI builders like Durable, Mixo, or Wix offer much better AI features, templates, and overall experience. Only choose Hostwinds if you already use their hosting."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Can I export my Hostwinds website?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "No, Hostwinds doesn't offer code export. Your website is hosted on their platform and cannot be exported. You'll need to rebuild if you switch platforms. For code export, consider Framer ($15-35/mo) or Webflow ($23-59/mo) instead."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "How does Hostwinds compare to Hostinger?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Both are hosting companies with website builders. Hostinger has significantly better AI features, more modern templates, and lower pricing starting at $2.99/month. Hostwinds is adequate if you're already their customer, but there's no compelling reason to choose them over Hostinger, Wix, or Framer."
        }
      }
    ]}
  />

  <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-12">
    <div class="mb-12">
      <p class="text-orange-600 font-semibold mb-4">REVIEW</p>
      <h1 class="text-4xl sm:text-5xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6">{reviewData.title} Review</h1>
      <p class="text-xl text-gray-600 mb-6">{reviewData.description}</p>
      <div class="flex items-center gap-4 text-sm text-gray-500 mb-6">
        <span>Updated: {reviewData.date}</span>
        <span>-</span>
        <span>{reviewData.testingTime} of hands-on testing</span>
      </div>
      <TestingBadge score={reviewData.score} />
    </div>

    <!-- TESTING EVIDENCE -->
    <TestingEvidence tool={reviewData.title} evidences={testingEvidences} />

    <!-- UNEXPECTED FINDINGS -->
    <div class="mb-12">
      <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-slate-50 to-gray-100 border-[3px] border-slate-300 p-6 md:p-8">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-2">Unexpected Findings After 18 Hours</h2>
        <p class="text-xs text-gray-500 mb-6 uppercase tracking-wider font-black">What nobody tells you about Hostwinds</p>

        <div class="space-y-4">
          <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-slate-600 font-black text-xl flex-shrink-0">!</span>
            <div>
              <p class="font-black text-gray-900">Client with 50 domains stuck - migration cost > value</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mt-1">Hosting 3 years, domains + email there. Built site, looked dated. Can't modernize due to limited customization. Moving 50 domains + email accounts? Too expensive. Stuck with mediocre builder.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-slate-600 font-black text-xl flex-shrink-0">!</span>
            <div>
              <p class="font-black text-gray-900">"AI generator" = template selector with 3 questions, no content</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mt-1">Expected Durable/Framer AI. Got template selector from 2017. No content generation, no intelligence. Durable: real content in 30s. Hostwinds: false advertising.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-slate-600 font-black text-xl flex-shrink-0">!</span>
            <div>
              <p class="font-black text-gray-900">PageSpeed 48/100 mobile - client: "Why is my site so slow?"</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mt-1">Simple 5-page site. PageSpeed: 48/100 mobile, 55/100 desktop. No optimization control - can't minify, optimize images, change loading order. Had to migrate to improve scores.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-slate-600 font-black text-xl flex-shrink-0">!</span>
            <div>
              <p class="font-black text-gray-900">7.2/10 overall, 7/10 existing customers, 5/10 new customers</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mt-1">Hosting companies know customers are sticky. Don't need quality, just convenience. Hostinger: same parent, $2.99/mo, better everything. Framer: $15/mo, modern design.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-slate-600 font-black text-xl flex-shrink-0">!</span>
            <div>
              <p class="font-black text-gray-900">"Fine" shouldn't be standard when better options exist for similar price</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mt-1">Builder works. It's functional. But "fine" is trap. Switching sounds like work, so you settle. If starting fresh? Zero reason to choose Hostwinds over competitors.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Quick Verdict -->
    <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-blue-50 to-indigo-50 border-[3px] border-blue-300 rounded-xl p-6 md:p-8 mb-12">
      <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-4">
        <span class="text-4xl">üè¢</span>
        <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-black text-gray-900">A Hosting Company That Added a Builder Because Customers Asked</h2>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-blue-500/10 border-l-[4px] border-blue-500 p-4 mb-5">
        <p class="text-blue-800 font-bold text-lg">
          Score: 7.2/10 - Convenient if you're already a customer, avoid otherwise
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="space-y-4 text-gray-700">
        <p class="text-base leading-relaxed">
          <strong>Hostwinds is a hosting company first.</strong> The website builder exists because customers asked for it. It works. It's functional. But it's not their focus and it shows.
        </p>

        <div class="bg-white/80 p-4 rounded-lg border border-blue-200">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 uppercase tracking-wider font-bold mb-2">The Only Use Case</p>
          <p class="text-gray-800">
            <strong>If you're already a Hostwinds hosting customer:</strong> Sure, add the builder. It's convenient having everything in one dashboard. But if you DON'T use Hostwinds? There's zero reason to start now.
          </p>
        </div>

        <p class="text-base leading-relaxed">
          <strong class="text-blue-700">The reality:</strong> Dated templates. Basic AI features. This feels like a legacy product from 2018 that AI was bolted onto. Hostinger has better templates and Framer has better AI at similar prices.
        </p>

        <div class="bg-gray-100 p-4 rounded-lg border-l-[4px] border-gray-500 mt-4">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-700">
            <strong class="text-gray-800">My honest take:</strong> Hostwinds is great for hosting. Their website builder is an afterthought. Use them for what they're good at (servers), not what they added because customers complained.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- COMPARISON TABLE: HOSTWINDS VS COMPETITORS -->
    <div class="my-12">
      <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-slate-50 to-gray-50 border-[3px] border-slate-300 p-6 md:p-8">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-6">Hostwinds vs Modern AI Builders</h2>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 mb-6">Hosting company builder vs. tools built for websites</p>

        <div class="overflow-x-auto">
          <table class="w-full text-sm">
            <thead>
              <tr class="bg-gray-800 text-white">
                <th class="p-3 text-left font-bold">Feature</th>
                <th class="p-3 text-center font-bold">Hostwinds</th>
                <th class="p-3 text-center font-bold">Hostinger</th>
                <th class="p-3 text-center font-bold">Framer</th>
              </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
              <tr class="bg-white border-b">
                <td class="p-3 font-medium">Starting Price</td>
                <td class="p-3 text-center">$3-8/month</td>
                <td class="p-3 text-center text-green-600 font-bold">$2.99/month</td>
                <td class="p-3 text-center">$15/month</td>
              </tr>
              <tr class="bg-gray-50 border-b">
                <td class="p-3 font-medium">AI Generation</td>
                <td class="p-3 text-center text-red-600">Template match</td>
                <td class="p-3 text-center text-green-600">Real AI</td>
                <td class="p-3 text-center text-green-600">Advanced</td>
              </tr>
              <tr class="bg-white border-b">
                <td class="p-3 font-medium">Template Quality</td>
                <td class="p-3 text-center">Dated</td>
                <td class="p-3 text-center text-green-600">Modern</td>
                <td class="p-3 text-center text-green-600">Excellent</td>
              </tr>
              <tr class="bg-gray-50 border-b">
                <td class="p-3 font-medium">PageSpeed Score</td>
                <td class="p-3 text-center text-red-600">45-55</td>
                <td class="p-3 text-center text-amber-600">70-80</td>
                <td class="p-3 text-center text-green-600">85-95</td>
              </tr>
              <tr class="bg-white border-b">
                <td class="p-3 font-medium">Code Export</td>
                <td class="p-3 text-center text-red-600">‚úó No</td>
                <td class="p-3 text-center text-red-600">‚úó No</td>
                <td class="p-3 text-center text-amber-600">$49 one-time</td>
              </tr>
              <tr class="bg-gray-50 border-b">
                <td class="p-3 font-medium">Hosting Focus</td>
                <td class="p-3 text-center text-green-600">Primary</td>
                <td class="p-3 text-center text-green-600">Primary</td>
                <td class="p-3 text-center text-amber-600">Secondary</td>
              </tr>
              <tr class="bg-white border-b">
                <td class="p-3 font-medium">Template Count</td>
                <td class="p-3 text-center">~50</td>
                <td class="p-3 text-center text-green-600">150+</td>
                <td class="p-3 text-center">50+</td>
              </tr>
              <tr class="bg-gray-50">
                <td class="p-3 font-medium">Best For</td>
                <td class="p-3 text-center">Existing customers</td>
                <td class="p-3 text-center text-green-600">Everyone</td>
                <td class="p-3 text-center text-green-600">Design focus</td>
              </tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>

        <div class="mt-6 p-4 bg-white border-l-4 border-slate-500">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-700">
            <strong class="text-gray-900">The verdict:</strong> Hostinger (same parent company) offers better AI, templates, and features for lower pricing. Hostwinds only makes sense if you're already a customer and refuse to migrate. For new customers, there's zero reason to choose Hostwinds.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- DETAILED TESTING SCENARIOS -->
    <div class="my-12">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6">Real-World Testing Scenarios</h2>

      <div class="space-y-8">
        <!-- Scenario 1 -->
        <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-cyan-50 to-sky-50 border-[3px] border-cyan-300 p-6">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-3">Scenario 1: Existing Customer with 50 Domains</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 mb-4 font-black">The lock-in scenario</p>

          <div class="space-y-3 text-sm text-gray-700">
            <p><strong>Setup:</strong> Client hosting with Hostwinds for 3 years, 50 domains, multiple email accounts</p>
            <p><strong>Decision:</strong> "Let's use their included builder rather than paying elsewhere"</p>
            <p><strong>Result:</strong> Site built but looked dated. Two months later: "Can we make this more modern?"</p>
            <p><strong>Problem:</strong> Limited customization. To migrate properly = move 50 domains + email accounts. Too expensive.</p>
            <p><strong>Verdict:</strong> <span class="text-amber-600 font-bold">Stuck with mediocre builder</span>. Migration cost exceeds value of improvement.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Scenario 2 -->
        <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-rose-50 to-pink-50 border-[3px] border-rose-300 p-6">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-3">Scenario 2: The "AI" That Isn't AI</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 mb-4 font-black">False advertising test</p>

          <div class="space-y-3 text-sm text-gray-700">
            <p><strong>Expectation:</strong> AI generates unique site like Durable or Framer</p>
            <p><strong>Reality:</strong> Template selector that asks 3 questions, then matches to existing templates from 2017</p>
            <p><strong>Test:</strong> "Marketing consultant in Chicago" ‚Üí Generic business template with city name swapped in</p>
            <p><strong>Comparison:</strong> Durable generates actual content. Hostwinds just swaps placeholders.</p>
            <p><strong>Verdict:</strong> <span class="text-red-600 font-bold">Template matching ‚â† AI</span>. This is misleading at best.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Scenario 3 -->
        <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-amber-50 to-orange-50 border-[3px] border-amber-300 p-6">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-3">Scenario 3: PageSpeed Disaster</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 mb-4 font-black">Performance matters in 2025</p>

          <div class="space-y-3 text-sm text-gray-700">
            <p><strong>Setup:</strong> Simple 5-page site (home, about, services, contact, blog)</p>
            <p><strong>PageSpeed test:</strong> 48/100 mobile, 55/100 desktop</p>
            <p><strong>Client reaction:</strong> "Why is my site so slow? Google says it's poor."</p>
            <p><strong>Problem:</strong> No optimization control. Can't minify, can't optimize images, can't change loading order.</p>
            <p><strong>Verdict:</strong> <span class="text-red-600 font-bold">Unacceptable performance</span>. Had to migrate to improve scores.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Scenario 4 -->
        <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-emerald-50 to-teal-50 border-[3px] border-emerald-300 p-6">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-3">Scenario 4: New Customer Starting Fresh</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 mb-4 font-black">Why choose Hostwinds?</p>

          <div class="space-y-3 text-sm text-gray-700">
            <p><strong>Scenario:</strong> New business needs website + hosting</p>
            <p><strong>Hostwinds pitch:</strong> "Everything in one place"</p>
            <p><strong>Reality:</strong> Hostinger (same parent company) has better AI, templates, features for $2.99/mo</p>
            <p><strong>Framer alternative:</strong> $15/mo for world-class design, no hosting lock-in</p>
            <p><strong>Verdict:</strong> <span class="text-gray-600 font-bold">Zero reason to choose Hostwinds</span>. Better options exist.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- FEATURE DEEP DIVE -->
    <div class="my-12">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6">Feature Deep Dive: Hosting Company, Not Builder Company</h2>

      <div class="space-y-6">
        <div class="border-l-4 border-red-500 pl-6">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">"AI Generation" (Not Actually AI)</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700 mb-3">
            Hostwinds calls it "AI website generator." In reality, it's a template selector that asks 3 questions and matches you to existing templates from 2017. No content generation. No contextual understanding. Durable generates real content in 30 seconds. Framer creates unique layouts. Hostwinds does template matching.
          </p>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">
            <strong>Generation method:</strong> Template matching, not AI<br>
            <strong>Questions asked:</strong> 3 basic ones<br>
            <strong>Durable comparison:</strong> Generates actual content vs. swaps placeholders
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="border-l-4 border-orange-500 pl-6">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">Template Library (Small and Dated)</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700 mb-3">
            ~50 templates that haven't been updated since ~2017. Boxy layouts, old typography, generic business stock photos. Hostinger has 150+ modern templates. Framer has world-class design. Hostwinds feels like a legacy product.
          </p>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">
            <strong>Template count:</strong> ~50<br>
            <strong>Last major update:</strong> ~2017<br>
            <strong>Modern designs:</strong> &lt; 10%
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="border-l-4 border-amber-500 pl-6">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">Performance (Critical Weakness)</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700 mb-3">
            My PageSpeed tests: 48/100 mobile, 55/100 desktop. That's terrible. Framer scores 85-95. Even Hostinger manages 70-80. Hostwinds has no optimization controls‚Äîyou can't minify code, optimize images, or change loading order. Performance is what it is.
          </p>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">
            <strong>Mobile score tested:</strong> 48/100<br>
            <strong>Desktop score tested:</strong> 55/100<br>
            <strong>Optimization control:</strong> None
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="border-l-4 border-green-500 pl-6">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">What Hostwinds Does Well (Honest Assessment)</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700 mb-3">
            Hosting infrastructure is solid. 99.9% uptime. 24/7 support is legitimate. Unified billing with existing hosting services is convenient. For existing Hostwinds customers who refuse to migrate, the builder is "good enough." But "good enough" isn't a competitive advantage.
          </p>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">
            <strong>Uptime:</strong> 99.9% (industry standard)<br>
            <strong>Support:</strong> 24/7 phone/chat/ticket<br>
            <strong>Ecosystem integration:</strong> Excellent for existing customers
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6">What I Tested</h2>
      <div class="bg-gray-50 p-6 rounded-lg">
        <ul class="space-y-3">
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3"><span class="text-green-500 mt-1">‚úì</span><span>Drag-and-drop editor</span></li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3"><span class="text-green-500 mt-1">‚úì</span><span>Template library</span></li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3"><span class="text-green-500 mt-1">‚úì</span><span>E-commerce features</span></li>
